Diagram 1 (Correct)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White's diagonal move at W1 is a severe move that aims at either connecting under or setting up an eye vs. no eye capturing race as matbogi.
\par
\par Black can do not more than cut off white at 2.
\par
\par Now, white thrusts in black's group with 3 and black cannot play dansu.
\par
\par Black dies in the eye vs. no eye capturing race!
\par
\par }
